{
  "texts": [
    "In experiment Exp2-(ii), the full GIX framework is under investigation.",
    "Here, the fine-tuning datasets consist of HPRD50, IEPA, and BioInfer.",
    "While the testing dataset comprises of sentences extracted from PubMed related to Bacillus Subtilis regulatory interactions.",
    "These two experiments demonstrate that GIX, using just a few target-related keywords instead of the manually refined and formatted sentences was able to maintain a similar level of accuracy of extracted interactions without losing any of the sentences.",
    "The GIX framework is therefore robust, because, despite the elimination of a large number (2,109) of sentences during pre-processing and the loss of Table 5."
  ]
}